'''emacs-shellfm''' is a tiny package designed to provide Emacs interface to [http://nex.scrapping.cc/shell-fm/ Shell-FM] console player.

= Obtaining emacs-shellfm =
Latest source code for emacs-shellfm is in [[MercurialMode|Mercurial]] repository at http://dzhus.org/hg/emacs-shellfm/ so you may get a recent version with the following command:
<pre>
hg clone http://dzhus.org/hg/emacs-shellfm/
</pre>

You may also download a [http://dzhus.org/hg/emacs-shellfm/archive/tip.tar.gz snapshot tarball].

See also project page on [https://www.ohloh.net/p/emacs-shellfm Ohloh].

= Features overview =

emacs-shellfm supports nearly all features Shell-FM has:

* Listening to global tag radio, group radio, personal playlist and recommendations, as well as «Similar to artist» radio and fans of artist currently being played
* Recommending current track, artist or album to your friends (with names completion)
* Tagging of current track, artist or album (with tag completion)
* Loving/unloving, skipping, pausing playback, banning current track/artist, querying for track info etc.

= Documentation =

Installation notes and usage tips are in [http://dzhus.org/hg/emacs-shellfm/raw-file/tip/README README] file (an [[OrgMode]] one actually) in emacs-shellfm source.

= Requirements =

Emacs-shellfm needs Shell-FM version 0.7 or later.
